column5: The lake is up a foot from last week. Lots of docks covered. Looking out,  there are floating   logs  and  debris. Boat safely.
Quinte was like running a gauntlet the last couple days. Full trees, logs, docks and anything else you can think of.
Watch out for drifting pontoon boats and docks.
They found it, one less thing to worry about! But the water is high!
They found it, one less thing to worry about! But the water is high!  I saw that, all ended reasonably well so a little twisted humor?
I was amazed at the number of docks floating where they should not have been yesterday and the number of cars/trucks trailering boats...must be opening of pickeral season in the Kawarthas...
